Division 4 - Government contribution to the Commission

101. Government contributions with respect to certain expenditure incurred by the Commission, &c.
    The Treasurer must pay to the Commission, out of money appropriated by the Parliament for the purpose, such amount as the Treasurer determines is appropriate towards defraying the operating costs of the Commission.

Division 5 - Borrowing powers

102. Borrowing debentures or inscribed stock
        (1) Subject to this section, the Commission, with the consent of the Treasurer, may borrow on the security of its revenues such sums of money as it may require for the purposes of this Act.
