    7. . . . . . . . .
    8. Contributions to operating costs of brigades
        The contributions required to be paid towards the operating costs of all brigades by insurance companies, the Treasurer and local councils for the financial year ending on 30 June 1995 are, notwithstanding the amendment of this Act by the Fire Service Reform Act 1995 , to be determined in accordance with the Former Act and the Former Act continues to apply to those contributions as if the Former Act were still in force.

